<TEXT>
the wife of a reporter who investigated 
the secret police for a prosolidarity newspaper died sunday after 
leaping from the window of her burning apartment the official pap 
news agency reported 
a solidarity official alleged the fire was arson and the 
government said it was investigating 
the fire killed maria jachowicz 49 but her husband jerzy and 
their 14yearold daughter jumped from an apartment window and 
escaped with slight injuries the agency reported 
jerzy jachowicz has written numerous articles for the 
prosolidarity newspaper gazeta wyborcza about the workings of the 
interior ministry which controls the secret police in poland 
at solidaritys national congress in gdansk delegate michal 
boni said it appeared the fire had been set by arsonists and 
proposed a resolution demanding an investigation into whether 
officers from the interior ministry were responsible pap reported 
the motion was sent to a congress committee for review the 
agency said 
a statement from the press office of the solidarityled 
government said an intensive investigation is being carried out 
by the police and prime minister tadeusz mazowiecki is being kept 
informed of its course 
earlier this month parliament voted to eliminate the dreaded 
secret police and to change the interior ministry into a smaller 
civilianrun office it had previously been staffed by uniformed 
functionaries along military lines and was considered part of the 
national defense system 
the secret police had monitored and harassed dissidents and even 
ordinary citizens to maintain the communist partys grip on power 
in poland the new office of state protection is to limit its 
activities to fighting espionage and threats to national security 
the secret police are suspected in scores of political killings 
and four secret police were convicted in the 1984 kidnapping and 
murder of prosolidarity priest rev jerzy popieluszko 
the government has said the secret police force was reduced from 
24000 officers in june to 3100 this year some reportedly took 
early retirement while others were permitted to transfer to the 
citizens militia after retraining 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

