<TEXT>
procuban guerrillas saturday night freed a 
prominent television executive was kidnapped in october in lima 
police said 
hector delgado parker owner of perus largest television and 
radio network was reported in good condition after being held more 
than six months by the tupac amaru revolutionary movement 
police said delgado parker was released about 745 pm but 
details of his release were not made available and it was not known 
whether a ransom was paid 
president alan garcia and interior minister agustin mantilla 
visited delgado parker at his home in the fashionable miraflores 
suburb five miles south of lima 
a videotaped message by a tupac amaru leader was broadcast by 
delgado parkers chanel 5 television station wednesday night an 
announcer said the broadcast was one of the kidnappers demands for 
delgado parkers release 
the guerrilla group began fighting perus government in 1984 
the group takes its name from an 18th century mestizo revolutionary 
who fought to free perus highlands from spanish colonial rule 
the group operates mostly in areas of perus northern and 
eastern jungle and occasionally bombs banks embassies and 
government offices in lima 
</TEXT>
