gymnastactress cathy rigby was injured 
when struck in the head by a sword during a performance of peter 
pan 
it took ten stitches to close the wound the former olympic 
gymnast suffered during a flying sequence in the third act of the 
play friday night at the midland theater 
thats why i guess you dont play with knives rigby said 
in an interview saturday before she appeared in a matinee 
rigby was suspended in the air to simulate flying during a fight 
with captain hook when her sword hit the set and struck her in the 
head near the temple said tom mccoy her husband and producer 
rigby bled profusely from the wound which eventually required 
10 stitches mccoy said rigbys head was bandaged and she 
returned within a minute for the final act he said 
im sure the audience thought it was very realistic rigby 
said 
as the blood flowed rigby said she thought how do we fake 
this one its not like losing a line 
