<TEXT>
erte whose pioneering art deco designs in 
graphics fashion and theater of the 1920s returned to popularity 
in recent years died saturday a hospital spokesman said he was 
97 
erte whose real name was romain de tirtoff was known as a 
painter sculptor lithographer and set designer he designed 
costumes for the legendary dancer anna pavlova and the 
performerspy mata hari 
the prolific artist designed every cover of harpers bazaar from 
1915 to 1936 
his most recent project was to design the sets for the broadway 
musical stardust some of his other major designs for sets and 
costumes included debussys pelleas et melisande and racines 
phedre 
he was also wellknown for the opulent clothes and sets he 
designed for george whites scandals the ziegfeld follies and 
the folies bergere 
he was just a genius said harris shapiro president of the 
dyansen corp gallery chain in an interview in los angeles i 
think history will reflect a few years from now that he was one of 
the greatest artists of the 20th century 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
frank j lausche a former fiveterm governor 
and us senator who was one of ohios most unorthodox and 
successful politicians died saturday of heart complications he 
was 94 
lausche lost his first two races for the ohio house in 1922 
and the ohio senate in 1924 in 1932 he was appointed judge of the 
cleveland municipal court in 1941 he was elected mayor of 
cleveland a post he held until his election in 1944 to the first 
of five terms as governor 
lausches long political career ended in 1968 with his defeat 
due mostly to a longrunning feud with organized labor in the 
democratic primary for reelection to a third term in the us 
senate 
he was the only ohio governor to be elected five times 
a conservative democrat lausche served in the state senate was 
appointed a municipal court judge in cleveland and was elected in 
1941 mayor of that city in 1944 he was elected to his first term 
as governor 
although a democrat lausche earned a reputation as an 
independent who often ignored party positions and consistently 
proved popular among independents and republican voters 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
horst sindermann a former highranking east 
german communist official and parliament leader died friday of a 
heart attack the official adn news agency said he was 74 
sindermann was a member of the ruling party politburo and 
president of the communistdominated parliament until november 
when mass demonstrations toppled the hardline leadership 
the son of a dresden book printer sindermann was jailed for 
eight months in 1933 for after joining a communist youth group he 
was convicted of high treason in 1935 and spent the next 10 years 
in nazi prison camps until the end of world war ii 
after the victorious allies divided germany into east and west 
sindermann served as editor of various communist party publications 
and held regional party posts until named to the politburo in 1967 
nine years later he became president of parliament and a member 
of the former council of state 
after the demonstrations that toppled former party leader erich 
honecker the communist leaders who replaced him purged many 
members of the old guard sindermann was stripped of power and 
party membership in november 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

