<TEXT>
lava flowing from kilauea volcano 
swallowed two more homes saturday and an evacuation order was 
expanded in this community threatened by the long eruption 
a 40footwide finger of lava which destroyed three houses in 
the kalapana gardens subdivision on friday set one house ablaze 
about 1120 am saturday said lanny nakano a civil defense 
spokesman on hawaii island 
lava destroyed another home in the subdivision at 6 pm 
saturday said wendell hatada another civil defense spokesman 
as long as the eruption continues the threat is real to the 
whole community said bruce butts another civil defense 
spokesman 
an evacuation order issued a week ago for 25 homes in the 
120house subdivison was extended saturday to 24 more homes butts 
said a 24hour alert remained in effect for about 40 other houses 
in outlying areas 
kilauea lava has destroyed eight homes in april including five 
since wednesday so far 87 homes have burned since the current 
eruption began in january 1983 said butts the volcano has caused 
more than 20 million in damage 
nearly all of kilaueas daily output of 650000 cubic yards of 
lava was reaching kalapana and the eruption showed no signs of 
easing said reggie okamura of the us geological surveys 
hawaiian volcano obervatory 
meanwhile state insurance director robin campaniano said 
insurance companies that cancel or fail to renew policies of 
homeowners in the volcanoravaged subdivision will be subject to 
fines or loss of their licenses 
also on saturday mount redoubt in alaska exploded with perhaps 
its smallest blast to date sending steam and ash 25000 feet into 
the air said geologist steve brantley with the alaska volcano 
observatory he said the eruption is significant because it is part 
of an unusually stable pattern 
</TEXT>
