mahoney her liaison with the state department about 5 pm mdt 
saying that a hostage would be released 
a state department official who spoke on condition of anonymity 
told the associated press that mahoney was relaying information 
given to us officials by the syrian foreign minister mahoney 
told mrs ronnenburg the state department had no information to 
contradict the report according to the official 
mrs ronnenburg said the mahoney didnt tell her which of the 
three prisoners would be released 
of course im hoping it will be jon but if its not ill be 
happy for the other families she said 
a proiranian group is holding turner along with robert 
polhill a business professor and alann steen a journalist 
hostage 
turner was one of four beirut university college staff members 
taken hostage jan 24 1987 
turner 42 an associate professor of mathematics and computer 
science at the beirut campus was abducted with three other 
academics two americans and an indian by men posing as police 
assigned to protect the college staff 
he moved to beirut from hawaii in 1983 his mother said 
turners lebanese wife gave birth to a daughter joanne on 
july 24 1987 five months after he was kidnapped 
his first wife ina clare turner lives in hayden idaho 
