republican gubernatorial nominee clayton williams 
disclosed that he paid prostitutes for sex a number of times in 
mexico and his native west texas a newspaper reported sunday 
he said it has been at least 35 years since he visited a 
prostitute and considered it a rite of passage 
why of course williams 58 told the houston post when 
asked whether he ever paid women for sex 
its part of growing up in west texas its like the larry 
mcmurtry book the last picture show the midland rancher and 
oilman said the book is about teenage affairs in a small texas 
town in 1951 
williams told the post he first paid for sex at age 16 
in addition to patronizing prostitutes as a teenager williams 
said he paid for sex while a student at texas aampm university 
williams who faces democratic state treasurer ann richards in 
the november gubernatorial general election and has campaigned as a 
lawandorder candidate said the disclosure has no bearing on his 
leadership capabilities as a mature adult 
prostitution is illegal in texas and was illegal 35 years ago 
it is legal in parts of mexico 
a call by the associated press to the richards campaign late 
saturday was answered by a machine 
the post interviewed williams at a posh desert resort in 
scottsdale ariz where he was spending the weekend for the annual 
meeting of the allamerican wildcatters a fraternity of sorts for 
independent oilmen 
the colorful millionaire never before elected to public office 
has sunk 56 million of his own money in an 8 million campaign 
williams came under fire from womens groups and political 
opponents last month when he jokingly likened bad weather to rape 
saying if it was inevitable to just relax and enjoy it 
the day after he made the remark williams apologized and said 
he realized his comment was insensitive 
during a visit to washington earlier last month williams told 
reporters he would feel uncomfortable running against a woman 
williams and his wife modesta celebrate their 25th wedding 
anniversary next month they have three children including two 
adopted teenage boys williams also has two children from a 
previous marriage 
as she did when her husband faced heat for the rape remark 
modesta williams stood by him saturday on the subject of 
prostitution the post reported 
what he did before we were married is certainly his business 
that doesnt bother me at all she said 
