a middleranking nigerian officer 
speaking on his nations radio claimed sunday to have overthrown 
the military government of president gen ibrahim babangida a 
western diplomatic source in paris said gunfire had been heard in 
lagos 
some radio stations outside lagos the capital of the west 
african nation appeared to be broadcasting normally and the 
majors claim could not be confirmed 
a man identifying himself as maj gigi oguaza oka read a 
statement on national radio in lagos saying fellow nigerian 
citizens on behalf of the patriotic and wellmeaning peoples of 
the middle belt and southern parts of this county i wish to 
happily inform you of the successful ousting of the dictatorial 
corrupt drugbaronish inhumane sadistic deceitful homosexually 
centered and unpatriotic administration of gen ibrahim babangida 
babangidas military government has been viewed as heavily 
weighted in favor of the moslem north since the forced retirement 
earlier this year of defense minister lt gen domkat bali 
a statement read on the lagos radio which was monitored in 
abidjan called on students workers lawyers and shopkeepers to 
take to the streets to support the coup it also said military men 
were confined to their bases and an overnight curfew was being 
imposed 
during intervals in broadcasts of martial music the radio 
accused babangida of widespread corruption and human rights 
violations 
babangida took power in a barracks coup on aug 27 1985 
