new outbreaks this month and the approach of summer weather have 
some scientists and growers in the nations no 1 agricultural 
state fearing the worst costly farm quarantines or even more 
serious foreign embargoes of california produce 
compounding the worries are continual protests against nightly 
helicopter missions that rain on neighborhoods a malathionlaced 
syrup that is a primary weapon in the medfly war new doubts also 
have arisen about government insistence that the eradication 
campaign is working 
the newest focus of concern is 10 fresh outbreaks of the medfly 
plague this month all but two of them outside previously treated 
infestations 
this is nothing short of a major crisis said entomologist 
james r carey a member of the states fruit fly scientific 
advisory panel 
carey and richard rice a colleague at the university of 
california davis believe the medfly has become established 
throughout california and that state policy requires an immediate 
overhaul 
i can think of no other explanation of whats happening 
said carey he believes the sporadic latewinter medfly discoveries 
portend an explosion in medfly populations by midsummer when warm 
weather increases the insects breeding rates 
if your house is on fire and the fire starts in the kitchen 
you dont wait until it gets to the bedroom before you call the 
fire department rice said were in deep trouble right now 
the mediterranean fruit fly is considered one of the most 
serious agricultural pests in the world 
the insect smaller than a house fly lays its eggs in more than 
250 varieties of fruits vegetables and nuts within several days 
the larvae hatch and feed on the fruit turning it into an 
inedible unsaleable mush the 198182 outbreak in the state and 
resulting quarantines cost growers 100 million while another 100 
million was spent on eradication 
in a march 26 memo circulated among top agriculture officials 
carey argues that a new longrange and aggressive strategy must be 
adopted to get rid of the medfly this time around 
i feel that a program designed to eradicate the medfly must be 
viewed as similar to those designed to eradicate major diseases 
such as smallpox or malaria carey wrote 
carey recommends a new research effort to develop better tools 
to detect and exterminate the medfly 
nevertheless officials at the california department of food and 
agriculture maintain that the 365 million medfly eradication 
program is working 
dr carey has not produced any scientific data to prove his 
hypothesis said isi siddiqui an assistant director of the 
department and as a state official who supervises the war against 
the medfly siddiqui said he must have proof before ordering a new 
strategy 
obviously we are experiencing more difficulties than we 
expected siddiqui acknowledged but he said the treatment 
program which mostly uses aerial pesticide spraying and the 
release of millions of sterile medflies will eventually wipe out 
the cropdestroying pest 
gov george deukmejian added his support thursday saying the 
department of agriculture is pursuing what is a timetested method 
of eradicating the medfly 
other scientists on the states fivemember advisory panel also 
have failed to be persuaded by carey and rice said chairman roy 
cunningham 
these finds are of course discouraging but they arent really 
supportive of careys thesis cunningham said 
still cunningham acknowledged that he doesnt entirely 
understand whats happening 
everyone agrees that a fundamental problem in determining the 
extent of the infestation is the uncertainty of methods used to 
detect fruit flies 
a variety of medfly traps some baited with sex lures and others 
with food are set out throughout southern california 
but some studies suggest most medflies ignore the traps and for 
each medfly caught in a trap scientists estimate 500 to 1000 
other medflies are still loose in the vicinity 
if you ask my wish list i think id like to see a more 
effective lure that attracts the flies siddiqui said 
the scientific debate however has left farmers wondering whom 
to believe and fearing what more outbreaks may lead to 
sure you dread it said mike stuart a spokesman for the 
irvinebased western growers association if your orchard or your 
packing house or your farm is unlucky enough to be inside a 
quarantine area on the basis of a fly find its a nightmare 
the new medfly discoveries prompted agriculture officials to 
order aerial spraying in several new areas including 19 square 
miles in the riverside county community of woodcrest about 55 
miles east of los angeles 
agriculture officials also plan to establish a quarantine for 84 
square miles around the pesticide treatment zone including some 
3000 of riverside countys 37000 acres of citrus groves 
