polands partially free parliamentary elections last june were 
part of a historic and at the time unprecedented powersharing 
compromise with communist authorities 
in the elections the solidarityled opposition was allowed to 
compete for 35 percent of the seats in the lower house of 
parliament and all the seats in the newly created senate 
solidarity won all but one of the seats it could compete for and 
went on to form a new alliance with two smaller formerly 
procommunist parties to take control of the government 
