the killing of the seventh cabbie in just over 
six weeks prompted mayor david dinkins on sunday to order 
steppedup police action including undercover officers as drivers 
dinkins called the killings a public crisis and a threat 
to the entire city 
police say believe one killer was responsible for the killings 
of three cab drivers earlier in the bronx presumably during 
robbery attempts 
they were trying to determine if killings sunday in the bronx 
and saturday in brooklyn were related investigators have said they 
are unsure if two other earlier killings are related 
all but one of the drivers killed worked for car services which 
generally dispatch cabs to pick up customers who telephone that is 
distinct from the socalled yellow or medallion cabs which make up 
the bulk of the citys fleet and which cruise the streets looking 
for passengers 
