here is the text of the editorial in 
mondays edition of the englishlanguage tehran times daily on the 
hostage issue the iranian newspaper often reflects the views of 
irans president hashemi rafsanjani 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the release of the first western hostage in beirut is now a 
reality this necessitates that those involved should now even 
enhance their wellintentioned common moves and cooperation and 
expedite their efforts to ensure the continuation of the release 
process for all the hostages 
undoubtedly and for a fact the settlement of the hostage issue 
in lebanon and occupied palestine is beyond any single country it 
requires an allout effort on the part of all the concerned parties 
the islamic republic in using its spiritual clout along this 
line virtually left no stone unturned 
the iranians painstaking and continuous efforts in this 
connection over the recent months have actually proven that the 
whole thing is a highly complicated matter 
one just cannot hope to achieve anything without paying due 
attention to the rightful demands of the lebanese groups involved 
the tehran times believes that to contribute to the 
establishment of a general atmosphere of trust the lebanese groups 
should release another american hostage 
by doing so they once more prove their goodwill and 
preparedness for the settlement of the issue 
the lebanese groups will certainly find it hard to comply with 
this request and their position is quite understandable 
but perhaps the release of one hostage alone will not be enough 
to establish the kind of overwhelming trust needed to bring the 
whole hostage crisis to an end 
but for both the lebanese groups and the islamic republic 
officials it is islamic and humane considerations that count most 
goodwill should not come from one side only it is a twoway 
street 
the tehran times however from the very beginning has believed 
in the unconditional freedom of all hostages on islamic and 
humanitarian grounds only 
this daily believes that the release process must be expedited 
by acts of goodwill by the concerned party on the other side 
to negotiate with lebanese groups which have been subject to 
all kinds of hardship under israeli aggression and while scores of 
their brothers are held in captivity in lebanon and occupied 
palestine is certainly not an easy task 
their trampled rights should never be eclipsed by anything even 
the islamic republic will not succeed in its efforts to get the 
hostages released if it fails to consider the rightful demands of 
these oppressed groups 
but if the other party too displays its goodwill iranian 
efforts can be facilitated to ensure the release of all hostages in 
1990 
we do believe that the lebanese groups should still free a 
second american hostage with no preconditions this they should do 
swiftly in order to leave the ball in the other partys court to 
demonstrate its goodwill if it has any 
in fact the iranian people and government have no faith in the 
us administration but perhaps it is now time to test president 
bushs claims that goodwill begets goodwill 
</TEXT>
