that has to stop 
in washington secretary of state james baker iii reaffirmed the 
administrations position against making deals for hostages 
our policy is that we do not negotiate with hostageholders 
and we do not make deals for hostages he said and the reason 
we dont is because we think that will simply lead to more and more 
hostagetaking 
bush himself made no further comments upon his return to the 
white house sunday evening 
notwithstanding the administrations posture rep lee hamilton 
dind chairman of the house foreign affairs subcommittee on the 
