<TEXT>
if a catholic priest from new york has his 
way philip morris cos will stop making and selling cigarettes by 
the year 2000 
the rev michael crosby successed in getting a nocigarettes 
resolution introduced at the 1990 annual meeting of the maker of 
marlboros after two years of failed legal attempts 
shareholders will vote on the issue thursday during the new 
yorkbased food and tobacco companys annual meeting in richmond 
we know the cards are stacked against us said crosby who 
coordinates the interfaith center on corporate responsibility in 
new york 
not surprisingly management of the multibilliondollar company 
is urging stockholders to vote against the resolution which is 
included in philip morris proxy statement 
the cigarette business is the companys original core 
