business managements statement said 
it is a major contributor to the companys profitability 
the company said the board believes that the proposal is 
illconceived and would be highly detrimental to the company 
in 1989 179 billion or 39 percent of philip morris 448 
billion in revenue came from domestic and foreign tobacco 
operations the rest came from the companys interest in beer 
food real estate and financial services 
philip morris has moved away from tobacco and into other 
businesses with its purchases of kraft and general foods which 
together form the largest food company in the united states and 
canada 
philip morris which operates a cigarette factory in richmond 
has 11 percent of the world market for cigarettes its marlboro 
brand is the worlds bestselling consumer packaged product 
